My dad prepared a bunch of stuff for your parents, telling me to bring them all.

308
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:31,400
- What are these? 
 - There's something for Xiao Ye and your grandpa.

309
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:34,800
Chat in the car, or you'll miss the train.

310
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,700
Got it.

311
00:20:37,836 --> 00:20:39,956
Thank you.

312
00:20:46,588 --> 00:20:49,528
   

313
00:20:54,496 --> 00:20:56,100
Come in.

314
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,400
- Any pair is okay? 
 - Change your shoes, here.

315
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,210
Thank you.

316
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,660
Mom.

317
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:16,300
Mom.

318
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,800
Hello, Auntie.

319
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,600
Mom, this is Xiao Que.

320
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:26,730
Hello, Auntie. I'm An Zhique. You can call me Xiao Que.

321
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,800
Lin Tuo has mentioned you.

322
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:34,400
This is what Xiao Que and her dad had prepared, a luggage of gifts.

323
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,500
Thank you for these.

324
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,200
Not at all.

325
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:41,600
- How come you're here? 
 - What? Am I not welcomed?

326
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,700
Rolled pancakes for you.

327
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,200
I don't like them.

328
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:48,700
Fine. Give them back to me.

329
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,900
I'm going to the hospital.

330
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:57,600
You'd go visit grandpa, and we'll eat dinner together.

331
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,200
Okay.

332
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,500
Xiao Ye, finish your meal and don't be late for class.

333
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,500
I'll pick you up.

334
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,500
Mom, I can pick him up.

335
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,680
My brother can pick me up.

336
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,000
All right.

337
00:22:15,636 --> 00:22:19,336
- Where's dad? 
 - When is he home on weekends?

338
00:22:19,336 --> 00:22:20,900
How are you?

339
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:23,700
What can I say? As usual.

340
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:26,400
That's your room, right? I'll take a look.

341
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,900
Who let you into my room?

342
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:32,000
You have so many books here.

343
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:35,000
If I had worked half as hard as you, I would have gone to Tsinghua.

344
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,000
You?

345
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:41,200
Who do you look down upon? I was pretty good at my studies, and I got a high score.

346
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:45,000
Weren't you an art student? Why are you working so hard?

347
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,900
You should check my room first. Come on.

348
00:22:51,321 --> 00:22:53,441
Take a look at mine.

349
00:22:56,840 --> 00:23:00,176
Your room shows you were not a good student.

350
00:23:00,176 --> 00:23:02,576
I was not a bad student, either.

351
00:23:02,576 --> 00:23:04,196
I just loved to draw and play soccer.

352
00:23:04,196 --> 00:23:08,136
I used to make breakfast for the soccer team when I was a kid.

353
00:23:10,316 --> 00:23:13,056
Did you paint all of these?

354
00:23:13,056 --> 00:23:15,976
Yes, I lost many when moving.

355
00:23:15,976 --> 00:23:18,736
Look at this. My grandpa did the drawing.

356
00:23:18,736 --> 00:23:22,016
He draws so well. Just like the ones in the gallery.

357
00:23:22,016 --> 00:23:25,856
No wonder both you and Xiao Ye study art, so it's in the gene.

358
00:23:25,856 --> 00:23:28,196
We don't have any genes in my family.

359
00:23:28,196 --> 00:23:32,276
Wait, we do have some. I've inherited my dad's love for food.

360
00:23:32,276 --> 00:23:34,676
It's kind of a talent.

361
00:23:37,336 --> 00:23:39,956
Were you this pretty when you were a kid?

362
00:23:39,956 --> 00:23:43,356
Thank you, but that is Xiao Ye.

363
00:23:43,356 --> 00:23:46,176
He's quite pretty as a child.

364
00:23:46,176 --> 00:23:48,636
How did he grow up to be like this?

365
00:23:48,636 --> 00:23:50,456
You are so rude.

366
00:23:50,456 --> 00:23:52,376
Are you going to school?

367
00:23:52,376 --> 00:23:54,836
- I'm off. 
 - Wait.

368
00:23:59,876 --> 00:24:02,596
For you. I've washed it. Take it.

369
00:24:02,596 --> 00:24:04,376
This color is not my style.

370
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:09,216
Come on, just use it. This color is not easy to lose.

371
00:24:10,896 --> 00:24:14,616
- I'm off. 
 - Take care. We'll come pick you up.

372
00:24:19,016 --> 00:24:21,092
- Here, some fruit. 
 - Grandpa.

373
00:24:22,176 --> 00:24:23,240
Thank you.

374
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:25,860
I bought them in the morning.

375
00:24:27,016 --> 00:24:28,756
Do you smell that?

376
00:24:28,756 --> 00:24:31,016
I bought a lamb leg. It's being stewed in the pot.

377
00:24:31,016 --> 00:24:32,716
I love lamb the most.

378
00:24:32,716 --> 00:24:35,436
I heard him mention it. Try my cooking.

379
00:24:35,436 --> 00:24:37,836
Red wine braised lamb.

380
00:24:37,836 --> 00:24:40,256
This is his secret recipe.

381
00:24:40,256 --> 00:24:42,016
He cooked it for you.

382
00:24:42,016 --> 00:24:45,016
I must treat my granddaughter-in-law well.

383
00:24:45,016 --> 00:24:48,576
Grandpa, you've been busy since I arrived. You might take a rest.

384
00:24:48,576 --> 00:24:52,216
No. I'm so energetic.

385
00:24:52,216 --> 00:24:54,936
I'm so glad you're here.

386
00:24:54,936 --> 00:24:59,336
- Grandpa, Xiao Que really likes your drawings. 
 - Like traditional drawing?

387
00:24:59,336 --> 00:25:04,376
Yes. Your paintings are wonderful. Just like the ones in the gallery.

388
00:25:04,376 --> 00:25:07,916
All right, I'll draw one for you. Let's go.

389
00:25:07,916 --> 00:25:09,576
Okay.

390
00:25:24,232 --> 00:25:26,044
   

391
00:25:26,044 --> 00:25:31,928
   

392
00:25:31,928 --> 00:25:35,172
   

393
00:25:35,172 --> 00:25:36,256
Not so good.

394
00:25:36,256 --> 00:25:38,776
It's great. Grandpa, did you study this professionally?

395
00:25:38,776 --> 00:25:41,496
No, I never had formal training.

396
00:25:41,496 --> 00:25:44,896
My master was a street artist.

397
00:25:44,896 --> 00:25:47,556
He'd paint and write calligraphy on the street for money.

398
00:25:47,556 --> 00:25:50,616
And I learned from him with a worn-out brush.

399
00:25:50,616 --> 00:25:54,436
Later, I became a carpenter. Carpenters have to have some aesthetic sense

400
00:25:54,436 --> 00:25:58,056
to carve dragons and paint phoenixes on the furniture.

401
00:25:58,056 --> 00:26:01,056
If you paint well, it could sell for more money.

402
00:26:01,056 --> 00:26:04,976
Then I quit being a carpenter. But I don't want to drop the brush.

403
00:26:04,976 --> 00:26:09,456
Sometimes, I'd draw or write something as a hobby.

404
00:26:09,456 --> 00:26:14,856
When the two of us have a child, I'll let you teach him traditional painting.

405
00:26:14,856 --> 00:26:18,976
I'd love to. Hurry up, while I can still draw,

406
00:26:18,976 --> 00:26:21,856
give me a great-grandson.

407
00:26:22,616 --> 00:26:24,356
Copy that.

408
00:26:28,856 --> 00:26:32,370
- Xiao Ye. 
 - Xiao Ye.

409
00:26:32,916 --> 00:26:35,376
I bought you a hamburger.

