00:28:35,616 --> 00:28:40,136
There are so many emerging industries, so opportunities are everywhere.

452
00:28:40,136 --> 00:28:44,816
Right, the internet is developing quite fast.

453
00:28:44,816 --> 00:28:48,536
So, Xiao Que, what do you do now?

454
00:28:48,536 --> 00:28:50,816
I plan to start my own business.

455
00:28:50,816 --> 00:28:54,296
She wants to open a coffee shop and has found a place already.

456
00:28:54,296 --> 00:28:55,616
Coffee shop?

457
00:28:55,616 --> 00:28:59,996
Yes, I've been working part-time since high school. I can make a lot of cakes and coffee.

458
00:28:59,996 --> 00:29:03,016
Now I'm planning to open my own with my friend.

459
00:29:03,016 --> 00:29:05,296
With your friend?

460
00:29:05,296 --> 00:29:09,516
Kind of, she's a livestreaming host and we'll do it together.

461
00:29:10,816 --> 00:29:12,336
What kind of host?

462
00:29:12,336 --> 00:29:15,316
Selling products through livestreaming online.

463
00:29:15,316 --> 00:29:20,636
Selling some skincare products, food and drinks. Basically everything.

464
00:29:20,636 --> 00:29:22,856
It's just like the TV shopping.

465
00:29:22,856 --> 00:29:24,176
Yes.

466
00:29:24,176 --> 00:29:26,236
TV shopping.

467
00:29:27,376 --> 00:29:32,476
Yes, we get our stuff from the proper factories.

468
00:29:32,476 --> 00:29:35,610
All items are carefully selected.

469
00:29:36,256 --> 00:29:40,216
So, are you a livestreaming host or do you run a coffee shop?

470
00:29:40,216 --> 00:29:42,516
I run a coffee shop, and my friend is a livestreaming host.

471
00:29:42,516 --> 00:29:46,576
We can split the rent.

472
00:29:50,756 --> 00:29:54,816
- What's your major? 
 - Internet big data analysis.

473
00:29:54,816 --> 00:29:58,916
That's a good major. Why don't you find a job that's right for your major?

474
00:29:58,916 --> 00:30:01,936
I like coffee, so I want to give it a try.

475
00:30:03,596 --> 00:30:05,436
Do your parents agree?

476
00:30:05,436 --> 00:30:07,956
My dad is supportive.

477
00:30:07,956 --> 00:30:09,736
And your mom?

478
00:30:11,216 --> 00:30:16,296
She passed away early. It's only me and my dad.

479
00:30:20,376 --> 00:30:25,576
It's not easy for your dad to raise you all by himself.

480
00:30:25,576 --> 00:30:28,256
He is really amazing.

481
00:30:28,256 --> 00:30:30,636
Her dad is a particularly nice.

482
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:34,916
- What does he do? 
 - He drives a taxi.

483
00:30:36,116 --> 00:30:38,776
Hurry up and eat.
